info.title: CustomerInfoService-v2
info.description:
# Generic Response Body Every endpoints (registered and un-registered) will always have response body containing the operationResult object. This JSON object give information about what is the status of the operation call. Example 1 : ```json { "operationResult": { "method": "GET", "path": "http://localhost:8090/customer-info-service/v1/config/endpoints", "status": "SUCCESS", "code": "", "reason": "Data successfully retrieved" } } ``` Example 2 : ```json { "operationResult": { "method": "PUT", "path": "http://localhost:8090/customer-info-service/v1/config/endpoints/8d2773e8-04e8-4f4a-a38a-6", "status": "WARN", "code": "CIS0004", "reason": "CIS0004 | Resource doesn't exist : 8d2773e8-04e8-4f4a-a38a-6" } } ``` The operationResult object will show information regarding : 1. HTTP method was used for request call 2. URL endpoint called by the request. 3. Status of the operation :
SUCCESS | WARN | ERROR 4. Code :
The error code or warn code. One single operation might have multiple different error or warning that could possibly happen. Hence code can be used. While success will not have any code since normally scope of success normally is for the entire operation. 5. Reason : The error code message or the warning message or the success message. List of error codes: Code | Message ----------------|------------- CIS9999 | Error. CIS9991 | Endpoint doesn't exist. CIS0004 | Resource doesn't exist. CIS9993 | Exhausted Resource. Try again later. We use HTTP status code : - `400 bad request` - for any business logic error or input validation error. - `404 not found` - for db record not found. This doesnâ€™t mean the operation was having error. - `503 Service Unavailable` - Certain resources are controlled programmatically according to the configured limit. When client request exceed the limit, it will return response code 503 and with code CIS9993 in the response body. # Generic Header API endpoints accept generic header `X-Apigate-CorrId` as the mechanism for tracking correlation id of process between different application. The value is in string format. The header and its value will be printed to the log. The header is optional. If client app sending request without the header, it will not be printed to the log.

OperationResultResJsonObj.title: Root Type for generic_response_body_operation_result
OperationResultResJsonObj.description: Every endpoints (registered and un-registered) will always have response body containing the operationResult object. This JSON object give information about what is the status of the operation call.

FieldActive.description: Define whether the record is turned on/enabled or turned off/disabled

FieldCachePeriod.description: Define the expiry of the cache. In seconds.

FieldCreatedAt.description: Define when record was first created

FieldId.description: Unique primary key identifier of the resource/record in database

FieldName.description: Short name of the resource. Max 50 characters. Alphanumeric, unique, case-insensitive.

FieldUpdatedAt.description: Define when record was last updated

FieldJsonPath.description: To find the json parameter in the json body to be masked

FieldMask.description: String used to mask. Alphanumeric. Max 30 characters.

FieldErrorCode.description: The error code or warn code. One single operation might have multiple different error or warning that could possibly happen. Hence code can be used. While success will not have any code since normally scope of success normally is for the entire operation.

FieldHttpMethod.description: HTTP method was used for request call

FieldApiUrl.description: Full URL of the api. It doesn't support query parameters.

FieldOperationPath.description: URL endpoint called by the request

FieldReason.description: The error code message or the warning message or the success message

FieldPartnerId.description: client app id. Unique. Max 50 characters.

FieldUsername.description: Username used to get the access token from Mobile Network Operator

FieldPassword.description: Password used to get the access token from Mobile Network Operator

FieldAuthKey.description:
Authorization Key used to get the access token from Mobile Network Operator.
base64 encoded string of `<consumer key>:<consumer secret>`

FieldRedisKey.description: Key reference for the cache in redis database

FieldTokenUrl.description: Url to do generete token or referesh token

FieldAtLog.description: Define whether http response will be masked at log

FieldAtResponse.description: Define whether http response will be masked at http response
